.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":9,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":18,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Nicholas Peyvre 3rd Baron Peyvre was born on 24 May 1318, in Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England, his father, Paulin Peyvre 2nd Baron Peyvre, was 29 and his mother, Elizabeth, was 20. He had at least 1 son with Margaret d'Arden. He died on 13 September 1361, in Staffordshire, England, at the age of 43, and was buried in Toddington, Sussex, England."},"et":{"24 May 1318–13 September 1361":"24. mai 1318–13. september 1361","1318–1361":"1318–1361","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1352–1429":"1352–1429","1289–1323":"1289–1323","1298–Female":"1298–Surnud","8 December 1323":"8. detsember 1323","1352":"1352","1361":"1361","24 May 1318":"24. mai 1318","13 September 1361":"13. september 1361","1337":"1337","1379":"1379","1323":"1323","1289":"1289","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","1429":"1429","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Toddington, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Toddington, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Toddington, Bedfordshire, England","Toddington, Sussex, England":"Toddington, Sussex, England","Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England":"Ampthill, Bedfordshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"24 May 1318–13 September 1361":"24. toukokuuta 1318–13. syyskuuta 1361","1318–1361":"1318–1361","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1352–1429":"135